Aviation legend Burt Rutan designed the GlobalFlyer for Steve Fossett's record-breaking solo flight around the world.
Fossett faced challenges during takeoff but overcame them to embark on the historic journey.
The lightweight aircraft, with a pressurized cabin and reclining seat, carries enough fuel for the 23,000-mile trip.
Fossett will pass major cities like Chicago, London, and Tokyo, testing his endurance and piloting skills.
The mission, funded by Virgin Atlantic, aims to showcase advancements in aircraft construction and fuel efficiency.
